description: The Natural History wing is in the process of being completed.  A few crystal cases contain some unfamiliar specimens.

Surrounded by dark paneled walls, this room houses several specimens as well as a large glass case in the center of the lacquered wooden floor.  Gold-framed paintings on all four walls depict a variety of different climates and terrains.  An oak-framed brass plaque hangs above the green marble arch that leads back to the lobby.
title: [Wehnimer's Museum, Nature Wing]
